quran[28]{c,v,t,f}:
  69,35,"So Today he will have no close friend here,",""
  69,36,"nor any food except the discharge of wounds,",""
  69,37,"none will eat it except the sinners.”",""
  69,38,"I swear by what you can see.",""
  69,39,"and what you cannot see!",""
  69,40,"Indeed, this is the word of a noble Messenger<sup>8</sup>,","[8] i.e., recited by Prophet Muhammad (ﷺ)."
  69,41,"and it is not the word of a poet; little do you believe!",""
  69,42,"Nor is it the word of a soothsayer; little do you take heed!",""
  69,43,"It is a revelation from the Lord of the worlds.",""
  69,44,"If he had falsely attributed something to Us,",""
  69,45,"We would have surely seized him by the right hand<sup>9</sup>,","[9] Or ""by [Our] Right Hand,"" i.e., Allah would have surely exacted revenge with might and power."
  69,46,"then severed his aorta<sup>10</sup>,","[10] i.e., his life artery of the heart; causing immediate death."
  69,47,"and none of you could have rescued him.",""
  69,48,"This [Qur’an] is indeed a reminder for those who are righteous.",""
  69,49,"And We surely know that some of you will be deniers,",""
  69,50,"and it<sup>11</sup> will certainly be a source of regret for the disbelievers.","[11] i.e., denying this Qur’an."
  69,51,"And this<sup>12</sup> is indeed the absolute truth.","[12] i.e., this Qur’an."
  69,52,"So glorify the name of your Lord, the Most Great.",""
  70,1,"A challenger asked for a punishment bound to come<sup>1</sup>","[1] In the Hereafter. The pagans of Makkah had challenged the Prophet (ﷺ) in ridicule by asking Allah to bring upon them His punishment. See 8:32."
  70,2,"upon the disbelievers, which none can avert,",""
  70,3,"from Allah, Lord of the pathways of ascent,",""
  70,4,"by which the angels and the Spirit<sup>2</sup> will ascend to Him on a Day<sup>3</sup> the length of which is fifty thousand years.","[2] i.e., the angel Gabriel.\n [3] The Day of Judgment will be an extremely long day."
  70,5,"So be patient [O Prophet] with beautiful patience.",""
  70,6,"Indeed, they see this [punishment] far off,",""
  70,7,"but We see it to be close at hand.",""
  70,8,"On the Day when the sky will be like molten brass<sup>4</sup>","[4] Or ""murky oil."""
  70,9,"and the mountains will be like dyed wool<sup>5</sup>,","[5] While disintegrating."
  70,10,"and no close friend will ask about another,",""
